    <!-- Kudos -->
    <section class="section-panel">
      <span class="outline-text outline-text--right" aria-hidden="true">Kudos</span>
      <div class="section-inner">
        <h2 class="section-title" data-aos="morph-up" data-aos-duration="800">Kudos</h2>
        <div class="kudos-content">
          <p class="kudos_section-content" data-aos="reveal-left" data-aos-duration="800">
            Good work doesn't happen in isolation — and I'll be the first to admit that. I've only included
            work I had a large hand in, but whether it's <strong>design</strong>, <strong>ideas</strong>,
            <strong>UX</strong>, <strong>process</strong>, <strong>software engineering</strong>,
            <strong>mentorship</strong>, <strong>advice</strong>, or <strong>creative direction</strong>,
            the following people have shaped how I think, how I build, and who I've become along the way.
            They challenged me, backed me, and left a mark I carry into everything I create.
            A massive, heartfelt thank you to
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kevin-juanillo-1835b9b9/" class="kudos_section-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Kevin Juanillo</a>,
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jamesolano/" class="kudos_section-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">James Nelson Olaño</a>,
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/marian-rae-alvarado-3057b8190/" class="kudos_section-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Marian Rae Alvarado</a>,
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/eric-francis-casaljay-461418150/" class="kudos_section-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Eric Francis Casaljay</a>,
            and
            <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ma-clarizza-folloso-ab418b1aa/" class="kudos_section-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ma. Clarizza Folloso</a>,
            the loml. You know what you did. Thank you, fam!
